[{"id":31232,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<p><img height=\"86\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6cea7244-5210-48d8-82a9-e4dcc95af70e-image.png\" style=\"float: left;\" width=\"304\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"55\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/612676f0-8b71-49ae-887c-435530dc2063-image.png\" width=\"258\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"64\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/874d223d-341e-4744-ac82-db6619f64de8-image.png\" style=\"float: left;\" width=\"288\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"65\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/04e0a3fa-3c22-416d-9f11-325a78433146-image.png\" style=\"float: left;\" width=\"189\" /></p>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img height=\"73\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/950a85bc-36c7-4cda-a925-3b5e656eabbd-image.png\" width=\"382\" /></p><p><br />Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></math>Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></math><br />Polymer of glycine and amino caproic acid.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2017 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31194,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;are correct","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;are correct","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi></mfenced></math> are correct","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;are correct"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Which of the following set are correct regarding polymer.</p><p>Buna <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math>&nbsp;is copolymer of butadiene <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo></math>&nbsp;styrene</p><p>Nylon <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;is condensation polymer of adipic Acid and hexanediamine.</p><p>Nylon <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;is fibre.</p><p>Terylene is fibre&nbsp;not thermosetting polymer</p><p>Buna-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math> is copolymer not&nbsp;Homopolymer</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31171,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["A(II), B(IV), C(I), D(III)","A(II), B(I), C(IV), D(III)","A(IV), B(I), C(III), D(II)","A(IV), B(III), C(I), D(II)"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></math>chloro<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo></math>butadiene can undergo polymerization to form a polymer known as polychloroprene. Polychloroprene&nbsp;is a synthetic rubber commonly known as neoprene.<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b3ed2d1f-3c27-4aa6-93b3-22b4b33bc44b.png\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 81px;\" /></p><p>Polyacrylonitrile (PAN) is an addition polymer. Addition polymers are formed through a polymerization process called addition polymerization, where monomers add to each other without the loss of any small molecules.&nbsp; Nylon-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>-nylon-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;Biodegradable polymer.&nbsp;Dacron is a type of polyester. Polyester is a polymer that belongs to the polyester family of polymers.</p><p>So, A-II; B-I; C-IV; D-III</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31201,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Polyester","Bakelite","Nylon-&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>6</mn></math>","Melamine"],"answer":1,"solution":"Novolac on heating with formaldehyde undergoes cross-linking to form an infusible solid mass called Bakelite.&nbsp;It is a thermosetting polymer that cannot be reused or remoulded.&nbsp;&nbsp;Bakelite is used for making combs, phonograph records, electrical switches, and handles of various utensils","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31226,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dL8l1rONBTlUydbu4oOVHxoEu79eO-G_CesyJ0OhK0w.original.fullsize.png\">","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/m9SZ6mIqFE99vQPg_7iZVHa2_UKsdVqI0KYNcbeDAZg.original.fullsize.png\">","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Qlm9I2T8ttqV8-6IOD7lE3dEmJuIkb8XG309-9lugR0.original.fullsize.png\">","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/uVHL-iTspdGudPQ9-TDlOaOrafeG73b5wM3ITK1MLec.original.fullsize.png\">"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/tGPgDTAP_C7kgYdZ9fOrv8jvc9MqYd-nYCr4jrCis1o.original.fullsize.png\">","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31211,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iv</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iv</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iv</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iv</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>(a)&nbsp;<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b76fe7c0-4678-42c8-8646-9369f3b4e0c0-image.png\" style=\"width: 94px; height: 119px;\" />Caprolactum is the monomeric&nbsp;unit of polymer Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></math>.</p><p>(b) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></math>Chlorobuta<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo></math>diene is the monomeric unit of polymer neoprene.<br />(c) Isoprene is the monomeric unit of polymer natural rubber.<br />(d) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>CH</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>CN</mi></math> (Acrylonitrile) is one of the monomeric unit of polymer&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Buna</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (24 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31205,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["PHBV","Buna-S","Novolac","Dacron"],"answer":2,"solution":"Novolac (phenol formaldehyde Resin) + Formaldehyde&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo></math> Bakelite","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (20 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31213,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["(A) is correct but (R)&nbsp;is wrong.","Both (A) and (R) are correct but (R) is not the correct explanation of (A).","Both (A) and (R) are correct and (R) is the correct explanation of (A).","(A)&nbsp;and (R)&nbsp;both are wrong."],"answer":2,"solution":"High density polythene: It is formed when addition polymerisation of ethene takes place in a hydrocarbon solvent in the presence of a catalyst such as triethylaluminium and titanium tetrachloride (Ziegler-Natta catalyst) at a temperature of 333 K to 343 K and under a pressure of 6-7 atmospheres. High density polythene (HDP) thus produced, consists of linear molecules and has a high density due to close packing. It is also chemically inert and more tougher and harder. It is used for manufacturing buckets, dustbins, bottles, pipes, etc.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (06 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31247,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["polypropylene","polyvinyl chloride","polythene","polymethyl methacrylate"],"answer":3,"solution":"Polymethyl methacrylate is hard, fairly rigid. It is used for optical lenses.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (22 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31252,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Nucleic acid","Polystyrene","Protein","Starch"],"answer":1,"solution":"Polystyrene is a chain growth polymer.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (07 May Online)","image":null},{"id":31225,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/uUL_dhYDiY8gQKz4Xxjll8zUIe0d_3lNsYaKCxrB0wY.original.fullsize.png\">","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/pBqFpIQKpExkkTWHyP0QGz22XLowjaH7W8g21H-D9Qg.original.fullsize.png\">","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Njb_KRIwBBPsluQRRY5R_73uW2MG1GKUXCTYUDUtuQY.original.fullsize.png\">","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Djv7xMtZOjSYTbL_90laRUyr1PrSUVRjPNS1-R9EcBo.original.fullsize.png\">"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/uVYSiv0IKh8WZfQscgtQc5HIUcPZS7c1LozLYb0wiSA.original.fullsize.png\">","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31218,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Bakelite","PVC","Nylon 6","Buna-N"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Thermosetting polymers are cross-linked or heavily branched molecules, which on heating undergo extensive cross linking and cannot be reused. Bakelite is a thermosetting polymer<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/830222da-c00d-4577-91d5-10925ec9ef9b-image.png\" style=\"width: 360px; height: 161px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31220,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Nylon <math><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mn>6</mn></math>","Neoprene","Buna<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math>","Teflon"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>In the condensation polymerization reaction, the elimination of small molecules such as water,&nbsp;alcohol, hydrogen chloride takes&nbsp;place.</p><p>Nylon,&nbsp;a condensation polymer, is made of hexamethylene diamine and adipic acid.</p><p>Buna<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math>, Teflon&nbsp;and Neoprene are addition polymers.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8468db6d-1872-41fd-9e75-3d191663fed2-image.png\" style=\"width: 379px; height: 336px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31172,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<strong>Statement I&nbsp;</strong>is<strong> </strong>false<strong>&nbsp;</strong>but<strong>&nbsp;Statement II&nbsp;</strong>is true","<strong>Statement I&nbsp;</strong>is<strong>&nbsp;</strong>true<strong>&nbsp;</strong>but<strong>&nbsp;Statement II&nbsp;</strong>is false","Both&nbsp;<strong>Statement I </strong>and<strong>&nbsp;Statement II </strong>are true","Both&nbsp;<strong>Statement I </strong>and<strong>&nbsp;Statement II </strong>are false"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Low Density Polyethylene&nbsp;is obtained by the polymerisation of ethene under high pressure of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1000</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2000</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi></math> at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>350</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>570</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math> in the presence of an initiator. High Density Polyethylene&nbsp;is obtained when polymerisation is done in the presence of Ziegler-Natta catalyst at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>333</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>343</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math> under <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi></math> pressure.&nbsp;Nylon-6 is manufactured from the monomer called caprolactam. The monomer caprolactam is heated at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>533</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>543</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>in an inert atmosphere, it polymerises to give nylon-6.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (11 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31240,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Nylon -6,6","Bakelite","Buna - N","Teflon"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Thermosetting polymer :A thermosetting polymer can be moulded into desired shape when hot, but once these get cooled and hardened, they cannot be remoulded again. An example of this is&nbsp;Bakelite.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (19 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31227,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<p><img height=\"136\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/37d10d93-285f-4701-92b5-d17b364dd877-image.png\" width=\"252\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"182\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/36d27e09-4002-40be-9c7d-168a00238858-image.png\" width=\"217\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"201\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f63bcdfb-9b73-4920-991c-df321f44cc6b-image.png\" width=\"241\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"147\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a67938a5-31f5-4093-9bd6-7ccd609e090b-image.png\" width=\"273\" /></p>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img height=\"369\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/25ca80b3-a520-4845-85f2-c83f642a303a-image.png\" width=\"586\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31182,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Ethane-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn></math>-diol and Benzene-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn></math> dicarboxylic acid","Propane-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn></math>-diol and Benzene-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn></math> dicarboxylic acid","Ethane-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn></math>-diol and Benzene-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn></math> dicarboxylic acid","Ethane-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn></math>-diol and Benzene-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn></math> dicarboxylic acid"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Terylene is a synthetic polyester fibre produced by polymerizing ethylene glycol and terephthalic acid which is obtained from petroleum.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/76c25b12-b858-4403-afc1-ee0ced40062c-9757583_S.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 293px;\" /></p><p>IUPAC name of the ethylene glycol is Ethane-1,2-diol and name of Terephthalic acid is Benzene-1,4-dicarboxylic acid.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31184,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Novolacs&nbsp;are phenol-formaldehyde resins with a formaldehyde to phenol molar ratio of less than one.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bce89a9b-2b73-4072-b431-73850e2406b7-image.png\" style=\"width: 487px; height: 280px;\" /></p><p>The rubber obtained is also&nbsp;called Styrene butadiene rubber (SBR). In Buna-S, Bu stands for butadiene and, Na for sodium and S for styrene. It is vulcanised with sulfur. The rubber is slightly inferior to natural rubber in its physical properties.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8e53b179-9e27-4ca1-a4f4-c730da7907a9-image.png\" style=\"width: 379px; height: 140px;\" /></p><p>Glyptal- a polyester is formed by ethylene glycol and phthalic acid by step-growth polymerization.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d5455332-73a6-45f9-9fd8-23abe21036aa-image.png\" style=\"width: 527px; height: 140px;\" /></p><p>Dacron obtained by condensation polymerisation of ethylene glycol and terephthalic acid at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>420</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>460</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>&nbsp;using zinc acetate and antimony oxide as catalyst.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4e850628-0f8e-44f3-a570-476eab17f3ea-image.png\" style=\"width: 566px; height: 140px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31258,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Neoprene","Teflon","Thiokol","PFC"],"answer":1,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":31215,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Neoprene","Buna <math><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","Nylon <math><mn>6,6</mn></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<table border=\"1px solid\">\t<thead>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<th>Polymers</th>\t\t\t<th>Monomers</th>\t\t</tr>\t</thead>\t<tbody>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td>1) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Buna</mi><mo>&#8211;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></td>\t\t\t<td><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>CH</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>CH</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>CN</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>CH</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td><br />\t\t\t2) Neoprene- <math xmlns=\"http:/