7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>963</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31251,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Styrene and vinyl chloride","Acrylonitrile and vinyl chloride","Adipic acid and ethylene glycol","Phenol and formaldehyde"],"answer":3,"solution":"Phenol and formaldehyde undergo condensation polymerisation under two different conditions to give a cross linked polymer called bakelite.\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ks9XxfbvjxwiPOcrYoHy9JsdYiizifITqLkpIjZmMF8.original.fullsize.png\"><br><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/uVwmwKbUyVqjPk6L36TrZxVER7s3h51nJQZTyB1f88o.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (12 May Online)","image":null},{"id":31228,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dffe9c7a-b485-4885-a447-763b4f0eb437-image.png\" style=\"width: 278px; height: 138px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0e00bccc-9d9a-47ad-acfb-0d0d7fb4199b-image.png\" style=\"width: 236px; height: 184px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4d458400-cd58-42ad-bc84-271375d5c4be-image.png\" style=\"width: 270px; height: 176px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/83a978e6-55c8-43ed-ae38-40fd637e64bb-image.png\" style=\"width: 262px; height: 152px;\" /></p>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Free Radical Polymeristation<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7a8b7426-389c-4a16-be1b-bc81ae761a3b-image.png\" style=\"width: 568px; height: 265px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31230,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/foPel0SZPQATBFkdRixFCerj-5SmwK262RFCI9NYAZU.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/UY477aHG5rtRz7JSJfOO3fxImem6gXNE7LaMhQuT2L8.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dOrk6Rc5Ktgg5ibS6xy-PzYfOWBMHVUGGtl4sKS6Gpc.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ezHP9KLHJsOUgJwqbW93U4B10D08ixAUAKUqgbr8dA4.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":1,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 1 Online)","image":null},{"id":31203,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Novolac","Buna-N","Acrilan","Neoprene"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Phenol</mtext><mo>+</mo><mi>HCHO</mi><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></mover><mtext>Novolac&#160;(Given&#160;structure)</mtext><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mtext>Polymerisation</mtext></mover><mtext>Bakelite(Cross&#160;linked&#160;polymer)</mtext></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31208,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e8b333d0-2e9b-41b2-bb82-ae570c27d5e7-image.png\" style=\"width: 191px; height: 85px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0e1937d4-dab3-4bb9-87d7-f4d4c396e7f2-image.png\" style=\"width: 432px; height: 85px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/cfd57551-9663-45f4-b6c9-d5c0d6521f37-image.png\" style=\"width: 298px; height: 71px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6eb9725f-9368-46ea-97b0-2f4b9c9f3a47-image.png\" style=\"width: 275px; height: 152px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>The structure of&nbsp; the neoprene polymer is as shown below.<br />It is obtained from chloroprene which is&nbsp;2-chloro buta-1,3-diene. It is an addition homopolymer with rubber like structure and properties.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/87f57410-e1e1-429b-b7ff-058a72574957-image.png\" style=\"width: 395px; height: 238px;\" /></p><p>Neoprene is a polymer of chloroprene which is chemically 2- chlorobuta - 1, 3 -diene (isoprene).&nbsp;Neoprene exhibits good chemical stability and maintains flexibility over a wide temperature range.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31236,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Its synthesis required dioxygen or a peroxide initiator as a catalyst","It is used in the manufacture of buckets, dust - bins etc.","Its synthesis requires high pressure","It is a poor conductor of electricity"],"answer":1,"solution":"Low density polythene: It is obtained by the polymerization of ethene high pressure of 1000-2000 atm. at a temp. of 350 K to 570 K in the pressure of traces of dioxygen or a peroxide initiator (cont).<br /><br />Low density polythene is chemically inert and poor conductor of electricity. It is used for manufacture squeeze bottles, toys and flexible pipes.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2016 (03 Apr)","image":null}]